    "Item-level content validity index (I-CVI) was then calculated for each item by dividing the number of experts in agreement (or disagreement) by the total number of experts.",
    "Moreover, to adjust I-CVI for chance agreement, a modified kappa statistic (K*) was computed.",
    "To ascertain the average number of items scoring 3 or 4 amongst the evaluators, an average scale level content validity index (S-CVI/Ave) was reported by calculating the mean of I-CVI values (sum of I-CVI scores divided by total number of items).",
    "RESULTSA panel of 36 experts, nine from each domain participated in the content validation process of the responses generated via the GPT embedded model and ChatGPT.",
    "Each expert evaluated 20 responses (10 responses per GPT model) in terms of relevance, accuracy, clarity, and up-to-date knowledge.The overall content validity of responses generated via GPT embedded model and ChatGPT was 65.62% and 61.87% respectively (Fig. 2).The specialty-wise percentage of responses with acceptable I-CVI values generated via both models are presented in Fig."
